omni-dev ai claude history sync - Exports Claude Code conversation history to a target directory

Exports Claude Code conversation history to a target directory

Usage: sync [OPTIONS] --target <PATH>

Options:
      --target <PATH>
          Target directory for the export. Created if it does not exist
      --source <PATH>
          Override source root. Defaults to `~/.claude/projects`
      --project <NAME_OR_PATH>
          Restrict sync to one project. Accepts the encoded directory name (e.g. `-Users-jky-tmp`) or a decoded cwd path (matched after decoding)
      --since <DURATION_OR_DATE>
          Only sync sessions whose source mtime is at or after this point. Accepts a relative duration (`30s`, `5m`, `2h`, `7d`, `4w`) or an RFC 3339 timestamp
      --prune
          Delete target files for sessions no longer present in the source. Only files matching `<slug>/<uuid>.<ext>` are eligible for deletion; `<ext>` is restricted to the formats listed in `--output-format` so artifacts the run was not asked to manage are preserved regardless
      --dry-run
          Preview changes without touching the target
      --format <FORMAT>
          Report format [default: text] [possible values: text, yaml]
      --output-format <FORMAT[,FORMAT...]>
          On-disk file shape(s) to write. Accepts a comma-separated list, e.g. `--output-format jsonl,markdown` writes both side-by-side [default: jsonl] [possible values: jsonl, markdown]
      --exclude-system
          Hide system-side events (system reminders, attachments, permission-mode, summary, generic system events) from the rendered transcript. Affects markdown output only — jsonl is byte-identical regardless
  -h, --help
          Print help (see more with '--help')


