Enumerates pages within a Confluence space

Usage: pages [OPTIONS] <KEY>

Arguments:
  <KEY>  Space key whose pages to enumerate (e.g. `ENG`)

Options:
      --status <STATUS>  Filter by page status. Common values: `current`, `archived`, `draft`, `trashed`. Passed through to the Confluence v2 API verbatim
      --sort <SORT>      Sort order. Common values: `id`, `-id`, `title`, `-title`, `created-date`, `-created-date`, `modified-date`, `-modified-date`. Passed through to the Confluence v2 API verbatim
      --cursor <CURSOR>  Pagination cursor (returned as `next_cursor` from a previous call)
      --limit <LIMIT>    Maximum number of pages to return per response [default: 25]
  -o, --output <OUTPUT>  Output format [default: table] [possible values: table, json, yaml, yamls, jsonl]
  -h, --help             Print help (see more with '--help')


