omni-dev atlassian jira write - Pushes content to a JIRA issue

Pushes content to a JIRA issue

Usage: write [OPTIONS] <KEY> [FILE]

Arguments:
  <KEY>   JIRA issue key (e.g., PROJ-123)
  [FILE]  Input file (reads from stdin if omitted or "-"). Pass `--no-content`, or omit when `--assignee`/`--reporter`/`--set-field` is supplied alone, to leave the description untouched

Options:
      --format <FORMAT>         Input format [default: jfm] [possible values: jfm, adf]
      --no-content              Skips reading the description and leaves it untouched. Use with `--assignee`, `--reporter`, or `--set-field` to update other fields without rewriting the body
      --assignee <ACCOUNT_ID>   Sets the assignee `accountId`. The empty string `""` clears the assignee; `"-1"` triggers JIRA automatic assignment. Use `omni-dev atlassian jira user search` to resolve a name or email to an `accountId`
      --reporter <ACCOUNT_ID>   Sets the reporter `accountId`. Same conventions as `--assignee`
      --set-field <NAME=VALUE>  Set a custom field inline: `--set-field "NAME=VALUE"`. Can be used multiple times. Values are parsed as YAML scalars (numbers, bools) when possible, falling back to strings. Overrides values from the frontmatter `custom_fields:` map for the same name
      --force                   Skips the confirmation prompt
      --dry-run                 Shows what would change without writing
  -h, --help                    Print help (see more with '--help')


