================================================================================

omni-dev coverage diff - Analyses diff/patch coverage from a per-line report and a git diff

Analyses diff/patch coverage from a per-line report and a git diff

Usage: diff [OPTIONS] --report <PATH>

Options:
      --report <PATH>
          Head coverage report (lcov / llvm-cov-json / cobertura)
      --report-format <REPORT_FORMAT>
          Format of `--report` (auto-detected by default) [default: auto] [possible values: auto, lcov, llvm-cov-json, cobertura]
      --base-ref <REV>
          Base revision to diff against (default: merge-base of `origin/main` and `HEAD`)
      --head-ref <REV>
          Head revision the report was measured at (default: `HEAD`)
      --baseline-report <PATH>
          Optional baseline coverage report; enables project deltas and indirect-change detection
      --baseline-report-format <BASELINE_REPORT_FORMAT>
          Format of `--baseline-report` (auto-detected by default) [default: auto] [possible values: auto, lcov, llvm-cov-json, cobertura]
      --format <FORMAT>
          Output format [default: markdown] [possible values: markdown, yaml, json]
      --fail-under-patch <PCT>
          Fail (non-zero exit) when patch coverage is below this percentage
      --strip-prefix <PATH>
          Override the path prefix stripped from report file paths to make them repo-relative (default: the repository working directory)
      --collapse-ranges
          Collapse consecutive uncovered new lines into ranges (e.g. `9-11`)
      --all-files
          Report per-file deltas and indirect changes for ALL files, not just the ones this diff touches
      --artifact-url <URL>
          Link to the full coverage-summary artifact (markdown footer)
      --run-url <URL>
          Link to the CI run (markdown footer)
      --base-sha <SHA>
          Base (merge-base) commit SHA shown in the markdown `Comparing` line
      --head-sha <SHA>
          Head commit SHA shown in the markdown `Comparing` line
      --commit-url <URL>
          Commit-URL prefix for linking SHAs (e.g. `https://…/<repo>/commit`)
  -h, --help
          Print help (see more with '--help')


